			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	<strong>About Us</strong></p>
<p>
	The Onion, America&rsquo;s Finest News Source, is looking for a confident, assertive, and experienced <strong>National Sales Planner </strong>for our Chicago office. The most competitive candidates will display a strong understanding of The Onion&rsquo;s unique brand and readership and will ideally have comparable industry experience. This is a terrific job for a highly motivated individual with demonstrated technical skills.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Prepare and revise national ad sales media plans for The Onion and A.V. Club and ensure accuracy of placement details.</li>
	<li>
		Build sales presentations and proposals in KeyNote and PowerPoint.</li>
	<li>
		Assess campaign objectives, taking into account demographic and budget constraints.</li>
	<li>
		Aid team in managing online inventory for national sales programs.</li>
	<li>
		Pull analytics for proposals, using comScore and Nielsen systems.</li>
	<li>
		Assist in filling out advertising spec templates and answering questions about The Onion&rsquo;s ad specs.</li>
	<li>
		Assist in researching and developing competition trackers for National Sales team.</li>
	<li>
		Meet deadlines when creating proposals and resolve discrepancies in a timely manner.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>Experience</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Sales planning or advertising agency buying or planning experience preferred.</li>
	<li>
		Ability to work independently.</li>
	<li>
		Attention to detail a must.</li>
	<li>
		Excellent communication skills, must be able to think critically about both client need and internal solutions.</li>
	<li>
		Must be organized, efficient, team player and strategic thinker.</li>
	<li>
		Proficiency in Microsoft Word, Excel, etc. in a MAC platform required. Position is Excel heavy.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	National Sales Planner should be extremely organized, flexible and must exhibit the ability to react to request in a timely manner.</p>
<p>
	The Onion is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We offer compensation commensurate with experience and a competitive benefits package that includes comprehensive medical, dental, vision, group life insurance and 401K.</p>
<p>
	Please, no phone calls.</p>
]]></description>
