			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	<strong>Position Summary</strong></p>
<p>
	The Web Design Intern is responsible for assisting with the advertising / merchandising, content design and production. This position is based in our Chicago office and should help support and expand the Onion and its sibling websites. Moreover, the most competitive candidates will display a strong understanding of The Onion&rsquo;s unique brand and readership.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Job Duties</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Work with the Production Design Manager to collaborate with all markets, tweaking existing designs.</li>
	<li>
		Design graphics used for various types of merchandise (i.e. apparel, print / paper products, novelty items, etc.).</li>
	<li>
		Create online graphics as it relates to our Homepage Images, Merchandise Detail Images, etc.</li>
	<li>
		Work with the Ad Product Manager to quickly execute custom online advertising based on existing templates and assets</li>
	<li>
		Serve as a resource for any site redesigns and for the rest of the design department.</li>
	<li>
		Any and all other assigned projects or tasks, including Business and Content design projects, or other collaborative or longer-term projects important to either the local market, or broader Onion initiatives.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	Ideal candidates will have 2-3 years of in-school experience coupled with a college track in web/graphic design or a related field. Candidates should also have an eye for clean design, smart application of Onion tone, and attention to detail.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Knowledge in Adobe Creative Suite.</li>
	<li>
		Experience with Flash and basic ActionScript.</li>
	<li>
		Must have strong Photoshop skills.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	The Onion is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We offer compensation commensurate with experience.</p>
